snippet.textDisplay: Lost my Momma to cancer over a year ago..still fuc😤in hurts. barely see my friends anymore, Not sure what a friend is these days, and if I found one I don't know if I would know how to act. Social status means nothing when I am socially declined.. I used to be the life of the party now I think I'm just the weirdo. fell in love and still falling.. might hurt when I hit the ground if she's not there to catch me, People around me getting married, I'm in these weddings too.. and I'm happy for them, really I am. Not sure if it's for pity but it's not about me then now is it..these feelings of nostalgia, standing still while everything spins, ghostly memories of the good times fade right in front of me, still My heart somehow has so much love to give. God I wish I can give it to somebody who really wanted it.. and deserves it. But then again who am I? Am I anything special? Am I different or am I just like you? Only time will tell I will take my heart And it will travel with me until we find what it is that is looking for us 💜

snippet.textDisplay: When I was a teenager growing up in a small town and being gay felt sooooo alone. This reminds me of those times I would pray god to give me a person I could relate to and love. I was very depressed and thought of dying all the time and I remember on my birthdays my family would try to make them special and I would sit there as a shell of a person, sometimes not able to even pretend I was happy and when I would blow out my candle I’d wish for either happiness or if I was really low than death. I remember we were flying back from Hawaii and I was so unhappy and in my head was wanting to die and than our plane had a malfunction and started falling towards the ocean and I remember how scared I was and my family was on board and I didn’t want them to die and after they made an emergency landing and after that decided that neither did I.

snippet.textDisplay: Most of us long for a deep connection. From a young age, we’re taught to believe in a romantic love that will be all encompassing. But the reality is that it’s so hard to find. And even when we do, most relationships end and ultimately leave us feeling broken. I love how this song captures that desire for that love, that idea of finding someone “to die for,” and the loneliness one feels during the search. I wish our society taught us that not having that love is perfectly ok, that we can be fulfilled with ourselves, and that obtaining that feeling of love from a  deep friendship is just as valid.
